git:-
------------

1)New Repository and get that:-
------------------------------
->create a new repository.
->install git in windows or mac(xcode).
->then git clone that repository(then create react app).

2)Configuration:-
-------------------
->git config --global user.name "John Doe"
->git config --global user.email johndoe@example.com
You can use git config --list, or look at your ~/.gitconfig file. 
The local configuration will be in your repository's .git/config file.

3)checking in changes:-
--------------------------
->add gitignore file(ex:- /node_modules for ignoring node_modules folder)
->git status (to check changes)
->git add * (to add changes)
->git status to see the chages in red.
->git commit -m "message"(ex:-git commit -m "basic app added.") 
->git push(check changes in the git)

4)Creating Branch from master:-
-------------------------------
-> Create the branch on your local machine and switch in this branch(Switched to a new branch 'ReactListsNConditionals') :-
     ex:-  git checkout -b ReactListsNConditionals 
-> update the README file(only one file added i.e readme file):-
     ex:-git add README.md
->git commit -m "add a detailed description"
->git push --set-upstream origin ReactListsNConditionals
->now check in github.

5)clone a specific branch in git:-
------------------------------------
->git clone -b <branch> <remote_repo>
   ex:-git clone -b ReactListsNConditionals https://github.com/Nandini1Bag/ReactBasics.git



